# Basic Query Operations

## Overview
The Autotask REST API supports querying resources through GET and POST description: autotask rest api, using:
- Entity ID lookups
- Filter expressions
- Comparison operators
- Logical grouping (AND/OR)

## Key Concepts

### Query Response Structure
All query responses follow this standard format:
```json
{
    "items": [
        {
            "FieldName1": "FieldData",
            "FieldName2": "FieldData",
            "userDefinedFields": [
                {"name": "UDF1", "value": "Data"},
                {"name": "UDF2", "value": "Data"}
            ]
        }
    ],
    "pageDetails": {
        "count": 0,
        "requestCount": 500,
        "prevPageUrl": null,
        "nextPageUrl": null
    }
}
```

### Important Limitations
- Boolean values must be specified as `true` or `false` only
- GET query strings limited to 2048 characters
- Maximum 500 OR conditions per query
- User Defined Fields (UDFs):
  - Limited to one UDF per query for VB entities
  - Maximum 5 unique UDFs per query for C# entities
  - Case-sensitive when querying protected UDFs

## Basic Query Methods

### GET by ID
Retrieve a single entity by its unique identifier:
```
GET https://webservices[n].autotask.net/atservicesrest/v1.0/Companies/{id}
```

### GET with Filter
Query multiple entities using filter criteria:
```
GET https://webservices[n].autotask.net/atservicesrest/v1.0/Companies/query?search={"filter":[{"op":"eq","field":"isActive","value":true}]}
```

### POST Query
For complex queries exceeding GET limitations:
```
POST https://webservices[n].autotask.net/atservicesrest/v1.0/Companies/query
{
    "filter": [
        {
            "op": "eq",
            "field": "isActive",
            "value": true
        }
    ]
}
```

